    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but that's the thing. it doesn't feel like a retreat. it feels like a permanent vacancy. i look in the mirror and i don't see a person, i just see the machinery of a body kept running by habit. it's like the light went out in a house, but the house is still standing there, empty and cold, just taking up space. it feels so heavy, just being this empty object.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
