    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but why does the house have to stay standing if there's no one living in it? if the light is gone for good, isn't the structure just... kind of pointless? it feels like i'm just performing this act of being alive, but there's no one home to experience it. it feels more like a burden to keep the lights on in a place that's already dead.",
